Test Environment for SBLIM DHCP Instrumentation
##############################################################################

The SBLIM project offers a Test Suite to perform tests against the provider 
implementation and consistency tests against system values. These tests check 
the general functionality.


Prerequisites 
##############################################################################

- sblim-cmpi-dhcp package installed and configured properly
- SBLIM testsuite package installed
- SBLIM wbemcli package installed



Pepare Test
##############################################################################

The test cases are prepared automatically during the build process 
(configure step)



Install Configuration Files
##############################################################################

When using an RPM package, the tests will be installed with the 'test' RPM
package itself.
Using the 'TAR ball' or the 'CVS extract', the tests will be installed during 
'make install'



Run Test
##############################################################################

Run the test in the testsuite directory (typically /usr/share/sblim-testsuite)
by executing the following commands:

  ./test-cmpi-dhcp.sh
  echo Status: $SBLIM_TESTSUITE_RUN
